---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="Privacy Policy — Discussed" description="Privacy policy for the Discussed browser extension.">
  <article class="pb-16 pt-10 sm:pb-24 sm:pt-14">
    <div class="site-shell">
      <div class="surface-panel rounded-[2rem] px-6 py-8 sm:px-10 sm:py-10">
        <div class="max-w-3xl">
          <span class="eyebrow">Privacy</span>
          <h1 class="mt-6 text-[clamp(2.5rem,5vw,4rem)] font-semibold tracking-[-0.06em] text-[color:var(--page-ink)]">Privacy Policy</h1>
          <p class="mt-4 max-w-2xl text-base leading-8 text-[color:var(--page-ink-soft)]">
            Discussed is designed to help you find discussions about pages you visit without quietly turning your browsing into product telemetry.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="prose prose-sm mt-10 max-w-3xl sm:prose-base">
      <p><strong>Effective date:</strong> April 5, 2026</p>
      <p>
        Discussed is a browser extension that helps you find online discussions about the pages you visit.
        This policy explains what data the extension accesses and how it is used.
      </p>

      <h2>What the extension accesses</h2>
      <p>
        Discussed reads the URL of your current browser tab to check whether discussions exist for that page.
        No other browser data is accessed.
      </p>

      <h2>External services</h2>
      <p>When checking for discussions, the extension sends the current page URL to these services:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Hacker News</strong> (via Algolia Search API)</li>
        <li><strong>Reddit</strong> (via Reddit search API)</li>
        <li><strong>Lobsters</strong> (via Lobsters API)</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Before contacting any API, the extension uses a locally stored
        <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bloom_filter">Bloom filter</a>
        to check whether a discussion is likely to exist. The Bloom filter is downloaded from
        GitHub Releases. No user data is sent during this download.
      </p>

      <h2>AI summarization</h2>
      <p>
        The optional AI summary feature sends discussion comment text to the LLM provider
        you choose (e.g., OpenAI, Anthropic), using an API key that you provide.
        Your API key is stored locally in your browser and is never transmitted to
        any server other than your chosen LLM provider.
      </p>

      <h2>Data collection</h2>
      <p>
        Discussed does not collect, store, or share any personal data. There is no backend server,
        no analytics, no tracking, and no telemetry. All extension data stays in your browser.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        If you have questions about this policy, contact
        <a href="mailto:hi@discussed.dev">hi@discussed.dev</a>.
      </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</Base>
